post_text: We are thrilled to announce the 3rd annual Explorers Fair held on Oct. 17th from 5:00 - 7:30 pm at the Silver Dollar Fairgrounds in Chico. post_text: A belated congratulations to the February Staff Member of the Month, Ms. Bai Vue! From her nominator Morgan Iversen: "Bai is our Special Education resource paraprofessional who works with TK to 12th grade students. She also works with intervention groups and travels across the county to translate for IEP meetings. Bai is also pursuing her Special Education Credential. She expertly modifies student work and is always willing to help out wherever and whenever needed. Bai is creative, caring and always has a positive attitude. She is constantly a happy face on campus and has a great rapport with all her students and the staff. Bai requires minimal instruction and understands what is expected, always striving for success. Bai goes above and beyond in every area she works. As a classroom teacher I’m grateful for her support in helping my students meet their learning goals."

post_text: Congratulations to Mrs. Lauren Kelleher, our Transitional and Kindergarten teacher, on being selected the Princeton Elementary School Staff Member of the Month! According to her nominator, Agripina Rodriguez: “Mrs. Kelleher was nominated for her commitment and dedication to all her students. She is always on time and her lessons are well planned. She shows initiative in her planning and effectively carries out her responsibilities toward her students and the staff. Her ability to teach all academic subjects is strong while providing excellent educational opportunities for her new early learners. She cares deeply about her students and uses her kind, yet firm voice to create an environment that fosters success. She treats her students with respect and shows how she values them with her cheerful morning greetings every day. It has been my pleasure to work alongside a new colleague this year and I am glad to nominate Lauren. She is very deserving of this award!”

post_text: Congratulations to Princeton Elementary School's Staff Member of the Month, Linda Hansen! From her nominator, Theresa Zoller: "It is with great pleasure that I nominate Linda Hansen. Linda is a true asset to our school team in her role as secretary. She is self-motivated, attentive to details and skilled at both independent and collaborative work. Her warm smile and friendly personality create a welcoming atmosphere in the office. She’s always ready to assist students, parents, and staff in any way possible. Personally, Linda is a cherished friend and member of my family. We have job-shared for the past 18 years. I am extremely grateful to work alongside such a dependable and competent person. Our ability to communicate well and the respect we have for each other are the keys to our successful working relationship. Congratulations Linda! I appreciate all that you do for our students, staff, and for me."

post_text:
Congratulations to our Princeton Elementary Students of the Trimester, Alan and Abel!

In her nomination of Alan, Mrs. Bryant wrote: "It has been a great pleasure having the opportunity to work with Alan in 3rd grade. He has a strong desire to succeed and continues to make great progress in school. He comes prepared and ready to learn every day. He works very hard, takes pride in his work and never gives up. His sweet, kind, caring, and friendly personality is an inspiration to our class. I am proud to announce that Alan is the student of the trimester."

In her nomination of Abel, Mrs. Halley wrote: "Abel has been such a wonderful student to have in class. He is a hard worker and gives 110% in all his work. When he is not reading, he is more than willing to help his teacher and classmates finish their work. His thoughtful and caring personality are truly a treasure. I am very proud to announce that Abel is the student of the trimester."

post_text:
Congratulations to Dena Schmidt, our Princeton Elementary employee of the month! In her nomination, Sandy Houtman wrote:

"I am honored to announce my nomination for Employee of the Month at Princeton Elementary School as our Lead Teacher, Dena Schmidt.

Dena’s personal commitment and dedication to the success of our students, their education, and to our staff and school is outstanding and admirable. Furthermore, her winning personality is inspirational, and I believe the leadership she provides and the services she oversees have benefited greatly.

Dena is an outstanding teacher with an amazing vision and desire for excellence. Her students will forever benefit from her passion and enthusiasm.

Dena, I want you to know that I admire you and truly appreciate our friendship. You always make my days more fun. I’d also like to acknowledge and congratulate you on all the amazing community and volunteer work that you have achieved over the years.

Congratulations Dena… You are awesome!"
